@startuml
title Scientific Mode Architecture: Calculator with Scientific Operations Delegation

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor Black
    ArrowColor Black
}

class Calculator {
    - _history : list[dict]
    - _scientific_mode : bool
    + add(a, b)
    + subtract(a, b)
    + multiply(a, b)
    + divide(a, b)
    + square(a)
    + cube(a)
    + square_root(a)
    + cube_root(a)
    + factorial(n)
    + power(base, exp)
    + log(a)
    + ln(a)
    + sin(x)
    + cos(x)
    + tan(x)
    + asin(x)
    + acos(x)
    + atan(x)
    + sinh(x)
    + cosh(x)
    + tanh(x)
    + exp(x)
    + get_pi()
    + get_e()
    + enable_scientific_mode()
    + disable_scientific_mode()
    + toggle_scientific_mode()
    + is_scientific_mode() : bool
    - _record_operation(operation_name, operands, result)
    + get_history() : list[dict]
    + clear_history()
}

class BasicOperations {
    + {static} add(a, b)
    + {static} subtract(a, b)
    + {static} multiply(a, b)
    + {static} divide(a, b)
}

class AdvancedOperations {
    + {static} square(a)
    + {static} cube(a)
    + {static} square_root(a)
    + {static} cube_root(a)
    + {static} factorial(n)
    + {static} power(base, exp)
    + {static} log(a)
    + {static} ln(a)
}

class ScientificOperations {
    + {static} sin(x)
    + {static} cos(x)
    + {static} tan(x)
    + {static} asin(x)
    + {static} acos(x)
    + {static} atan(x)
    + {static} sinh(x)
    + {static} cosh(x)
    + {static} tanh(x)
    + {static} exp(x)
    + {static} pi()
    + {static} e()
}

note bottom of ScientificOperations
  Pure functions, no state.
  asin/acos validate domain: x in [-1, 1].
  Callable regardless of Calculator._scientific_mode;
  mode controls UI visibility only.
end note

note right of Calculator
  _history stores dicts:
  { operation, operands, result }
end note

Calculator --> BasicOperations : delegates to
Calculator --> AdvancedOperations : delegates to
Calculator --> ScientificOperations : delegates to\n(scientific methods)

@enduml
